      Southgate bottled this game tactically. He should have started with Grealish over Mount in 4-2-3-1. Instead of using England's best tactics to project their own personality and style onto the game he was running scared of Italy. He used 3-4-3 and England parked the bus and got completely dominated. The fact England scored with their first attack and had one shot in first 60 minutes but led 1-0 doesn't change anything. It was screaming out all game at 1-0 to revert to a back 4 but like the Croatia semi Southgate doesn't have a clue tactically or personnel wise. When he did change to a back four he negatively matched Italy instead of using 4-2-3-1. He also played Grealish on the left wing instead of as a number 10 when he brought him on which was a mistake. England missed Foden, but the reality is Southgate's fear cost England and the double sub before penalties and the personnel put on pens was questionable too. Italy and Mancini deserved to beat England and Southgate here.
